HEADWORD: Necrophobia
<hw>Nec`ro*pho"bi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>nekro`s</grk> a dead body + <grk>fobei^n</grk> to fear.]</ety>
<def>An exaggerated fear of death or horror of dead bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

